  "texts": [
    "Inspired by this, CODEAGENT uses a popular search engine Duck-DuckGo foot_1 to choose the most relevant websites, and then apply LLMs to summarize the website content as the final tool output foot_2.",
    "In the process, we block websites that may lead to data leakage.",
    "The usage pattern of this tool is formatted as: Web-Search(input_query), which will return the formatted content searched from websites.",
    "Documentation Reading Besides gathering information from websites, we also retrieve relevant knowledge from the documentation of the repository.",
    "To achieve this, CODEAGENT leverages BM25 (Robertson et al., 2009) as the documentation reading tool."
  ],
